{
  "text": "The Use of Mass Spectrometry in Characterization of Bone Morphogenetic Proteins from Biological Samples www.intechopen.com separation, and nano LC coupled to LTQ-Orbitrap peptide analysis. By western blot they have confirmed upregulation of IQGAP1, isoform 1 of gelsolin (GSN), moesin, radixin, and cofilin 1 (CFL-1), and upregulation of focal adhesion proteins FLN-A, LAMA1, LAMA5, COL1A1, COL3A1, COL4A6, and COL5A2, as well as the downregulation of COL4A1, COL4A2, and COL4A4. [CITATION_1] have studied heparin-binding growth factor 2 (HBGF-2 ) effect on osteoblasts.",
